Financials, Marketing and Sales

Marketing Your Agents: Effort vs. Talent

Leung, Fine F.; Kim, Sara; Tse, Caleb H.

When highlighting exceptional performance of real estate agents, firms often credit the success to either sheer effort or natural talent. The way in which you market your agents, though, can impact their relationship formation with clients and, ultimately, the success of your firm.

He is specialist in qualitative methodology. He has designed, coordinated and executed research projects for 23 years in various fields such as: adver-tising evaluation, engagement, positioning, branding, institutional and go-vernment image, impact of health campaigns, assessment of audiovisual products, enrichment of strategies for political, promotional campaigns, proof of creative concepts, tourist planning and agrochemicals, among others.
Dr. Claudio is a regular contributor of Mexican TV and Radio programs and has been a speaker at Advertising Week New York and at Advertising Week LATAM, as well as at various marketing, advertising and research events.
